                  A graph with a vertical asymptote at <m>x=1</m>
                </shortdescription>
                <latex-image>
                  <![CDATA[ 
                    \begin{tikzpicture}
                      \begin{axis}[
                        axis x line = middle,
                            axis y line = middle,
                            every axis y label/.style={at={(ticklabel cs:1.1)}},
                        y label style={at={(axis description cs:.5,1.1)},anchor=north},
                            ylabel = {\(f(x)\)},
                            every axis x label/.style= {at ={(ticklabel cs:1)}},
                            x label style={at={(axis description cs:1.1,.5)},anchor=east},
                            xlabel = {\(x\)},
                            xtick = {-4,-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4},
                        xmin = -5, xmax = 5,
                        ymin = -5, ymax = 5,
                        trig format plots = rad
                        ]		
                        \addplot[thick,smooth, samples=100, domain=-5:.99] {x/(x-1)};
                        \addplot[thick,smooth, samples=100, domain=1.005:5] {x/(x-1)};
                        \coordinate (a) at (1,5);
                        \coordinate (b) at (1,-5);
                        \addplot[thick, dashed,domain=-5:5] {1};
                      \end{axis}
                      \draw[thick, dashed] (a)--(b);				
                    \end{tikzpicture}
                  ]]>
                </latex-image>
              </image>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p>
          <ol marker="a">
            <li>
              <p>
                <m>\ds \lim_{x\to 1^-} f(x) = 3</m> and <m>\ds \lim_{x\to 1^+} f(x) = 3</m>, so <m>\ds \lim_{x\to 1} f(x) = 3</m>
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                <m>\ds \lim_{x\to 1} f(x)</m> does not exist because <m>\ds \lim_{x\to 1^-} f(x) = 3</m> and <m>\ds \lim_{x\to 1^+} f(x) = -2</m>
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                <m>\ds \lim_{x\to 1} f(x)</m> does not exist because <m>\ds \lim_{x\to 1^-} f(x) = -\infty</m> and <m>\ds \lim_{x\to 1^+} f(x) = \infty</m>
              </p>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </p>
      </solution>
